label.value: normal protein aggregate center formation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein aggregate center formation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Protein aggregate centers are composed of chaperones and misfolded proteins, and are reversibly formed in the nucleus and cytosol to shield thermosensitive proteins from degradation until conditions allow disaggregation and refolding.

label.value: protein absent from cell during heat shock

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell is too low to detect when the cell is subject to heat shock. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic metaphase with condensed chromosomes

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested in metaphase under conditions where arrest does not normally occur, and in which chromosomes remain condensed.

label.value: short bipolar mitotic spindle during anaphase

value.value: A spindle phenotype in which the mitotic spindle is shorter than normal during anaphase.

label.value: increased histone H4-K5 acetylation at centromere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 5 of histone H4 in centromeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K12 acetylation at centromere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 12 of histone H4 in centromeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K14 acetylation at centromere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 14 of histone H3 in centromeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K5 acetylation at centromere outer repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 5 of histone H4 in centromere outer repeat regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K8 acetylation at centromere outer repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 8 of histone H4 in centromere outer repeat regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K12 acetylation at centromere outer repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 12 of histone H4 in centromere outer repeat regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K16 acetylation at centromere outer repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 16 of histone H4 in centromere outer repeat regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K5 acetylation at centromere central core during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 5 of histone H4 at the central core of the centromeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K8 acetylation at centromere central core during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 8 of histone H4 at the central core of the centromeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K12 acetylation at centromere central core during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 12 of histone H4 at the central core of the centromeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K8 acetylation at subtelomeric heterochromatin during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 8 of histone H4 in heterochromatin at subtelomeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: altered level of macromolecular complex

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the amount of any macromolecular complex present in a cell differs from wild type.

label.value: decreased cytoplasmic translation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of translation in the cytoplasm is decreased.

definition.value: Note that this term should be used only when an experiment measures protein synthesis directly, e.g. by ribosome profiling or labeled amino acid incorporation. Consider annotating to 'decreased protein level' (FYPO:0000835) or one of its descendants.

label.value: abnormal stress granule assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which stress granule assembly is abnormal.

label.value: decreased stress granule assembly during glucose starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which stress granule assembly occurs to a lower extent than normal when the cell is subject to glucose starvation.

definition.value: Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: increased stress granule assembly during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which stress granule assembly occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: decreased stress granule assembly during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which stress granule assembly occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: decreased stress granule assembly during cellular response to heat

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which stress granule assembly occurs to a lower extent than normal during a cellular response to heat.

label.value: normal stress granule assembly during cellular response to heat

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which stress granule assembly is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cellular response to heat.

label.value: decreased level of histone H4 in cell

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of histone H4 measured in the cell is lower than normal.

label.value: increased tRNA binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which an interaction between a protein and a transfer RNA (tRNA) is increased. One of the relevant gene products may be encoded by the mutated gene, or both the RNA and protein may be encoded by genes other than the mutated one.

label.value: decreased mitochondrial tRNA 3'-end processing

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitochondrial tRNA 3'-end processing is decreased. In mitochondrial tRNA 3'-end processing, the 3' end of a mitochondrial pre-tRNA molecule is converted to that of a mature mitochondrial tRNA.

label.value: DNA content decreased during G0

value.value: A cell phenotype which the total amount of DNA in a cell is lower than normal when the cell is in G0 phase.

label.value: normal number of Rad52 foci during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sites at which the protein Rad52 (also called Rad22) accumulates is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased DNA damage at tRNA genes

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of DNA damage measured at transfer RNA genes in a cell is greater than normal. The number, extent, or both of damage sites may be increased.

label.value: sensitive to formaldehyde

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to formaldehyde. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of formaldehyde that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: normal growth on formaldehyde

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing formaldehyde.

label.value: abolished increase in protein phosphorylation during cellular response to stress in presence of small molecule

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which an increase in the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins that would normally occur when cells are subjected to a stress in the presence of a specific small molecule does not occur under the same circumstances.

definition.value: Use this term when a difference between wild type and a mutant is seen only when both the stress and the small molecule are present. An example is protein phosphorylation under oxidative stress in the presence of the small molecule INR119. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished chromatin silencing

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing does not occur. Chromatin silencing is the observed effect of processes that repress transcription in a region of the genome that is normally assembled into heterochromatin or CENP-A-containing chromatin (the latter is found at the centromere central core).

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792), and the biological process term 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828).

label.value: abolished chromatin silencing at centromere outer repeat

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing does not occur at centromere outer repeat regions.

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792), and the biological process term 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828).

label.value: abolished chromatin silencing at centromere inner repeat

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing does not occur at centromere inner repeat regions.

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792), and the biological process term 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828).

label.value: abolished chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing does not occur at the silent mating-type cassettes.

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792), and the biological process term 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828).

label.value: increased histone H3-K4 methylation at centromere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the methylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 in centromeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K4 trimethylation at centromere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which trimethylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 in centromeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased cen-dg RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which of RNAs transcribed from dg repeats in the centromere outer repeat region are present at higher levels than normal.

label.value: increased spatial extent of protein localization to euchromatin

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein localizes to a larger portion of the chromosome than normal in the euchromatic regions.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal histone H3-K4 trimethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which trimethylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased triglyceride level in lipid droplet

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of one or more triglycerides measured in lipid droplets is lower than normal.

label.value: abolished lipid droplet formation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of lipid droplet formation does not occur.

label.value: increased protein localization to chromatin at the centromere central core during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at the central core of the centromeric regions is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased euchromatin-derived RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of any RNA transcribed from euchromatic regions measured in a cell is higher than normal.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal growth during cellular response to DNA damage

value.value: A cell population growth phenotype in which vegetative cells grow normally (i.e. indistinguishably from wild type) during a cellular response to DNA damage.

definition.value: Use this term if you have assayed growth of cells exposed to DNA damage in culture. If you have assayed the response to DNA damage at the subcellular or molecular level, consider annotating to a more specific term (e.g. normal protein phosphorylation during cellular response to DNA damage FYPO:0002899). Also consider specific phenotype terms for growth upon exposure to substances or other stimuli that can damage DNA, e.g. 'normal growth on methyl methanesulfonate' (FYPO:0000957), 'normal growth during cellular response to UV' (FYPO:0000969), etc.

label.value: normal histone H3-K36 trimethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which trimethylation of lysine at position 36 of histone H3 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased histone H3-K36 trimethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which trimethylation of lysine at position 36 of histone H3 is decreased.

label.value: decreased homologous chromosome pairing at cis-acting homologous chromosome pairing region on chromosome 1

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which homologous chromosome pairing during meiosis (synapsis) is decreased (i.e. occurs to a lower extent) at a cis-acting homologous chromosome pairing region on chromosome 1.

label.value: decreased homologous chromosome pairing at cis-acting homologous chromosome pairing region on chromosome 2

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which homologous chromosome pairing during meiosis (synapsis) is decreased (i.e. occurs to a lower extent) at a cis-acting homologous chromosome pairing region on chromosome 2.
